Here the priest interposed. No catechising,
I beg of you, said he. It is my province to be
inquisitor; and I will inquire of our fair bride
here, whether you, Madame de Vamploise, have
given her fair play in your discourse, for I know
it is seldom that you give it to any body.
How so! Monsieur d'Abbeville?
demanded
