or goodness of that God, who, I know, is as able
to save in the whirlwind as in the calm. And, oh
Charlesmay I conjure you never to cease to
trust in him, and implore him to be your guide, as
well as your guard.
Maria, my sweetest love! said he, it is
my duty to do so; and since thou desirest it, it
shall be my study, it shall be my pleasure, my
Oh, Charles! she hastily replied; I trust
that it has always been thy pleasure. Oh, say
not that it is to gratify me that you would make
