off the vexation and chargin, which these little
cross-purposes to his wishes occasioned him to
feel.
At length all obstacles were removed, and
Washington set out with him to the cavern.
Maria had suffered much from her anxiety
concerning
the fate of Charles; but the attentions of
Tonnaleuka, who had industriously infused into
her mind the consolations of hope and of piety,
greatly soothed, and meliorated her feelings.
Tonnaleuka
,
